      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:6:113:2",
      "text": [
        " كَانَ أَمِيرُ الْمُؤْمِنِينَ ( صلوات الله عليه ) يُعْجِبُهُ الْبَاذَرُوجُ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad Bin Isa, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Hammad Bin Usman, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Amir Al-Momineen<sup>asws</sup> liked the sweet basil’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "2. Muhammad ibn Yahya has narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad ibn ‘Isa from ibn abu ‘Umayr from Hammad ibn ‘Uthaman who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said that ’Amir al-Mu’minin, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, liked al- Badharuj (sweet basil).’” "
        ]
      }
